ding similar brightness and\ncontrast in the images and separating the transient features. Moreover, SiRGraF\nworks better on low-SNR images of COR-1A than NRGF, providing better\nidentification of dynamic coronal structures throughout the field of view. We\ndiscuss the advantages and limitations of the algorithm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Jan 2022 07:48:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-09"}
